Question 

Vector Dynamic Constructor and passing object
Develop a class called vector holding size of vector and a pointer to actual vector elements.  Include a dynamic constructor to inialize the elemnts of the vector. Also write a member funciton that performs scaling of a vector for a given scaling factor. 

For example, <2,5,7,9,1> ia a vector with size 5 and actual elements are 2,5,7,9,1;  For a scaling factor 3, the resulting vector is <6,15,21,27,3>

 

sample input

5  // size of vector passed from main

2 5 7 9 1 // vector elements enterred by the user

3 // scaling factor

output

6 15 21 27 3

CODE
#include <iostream>
using namespace std;
// 1,2,3,4,5,
class myvector
{
       int size;
       int *p;
       int sc ;
       public:
       myvector()
       {
           cin>>size;
           p=new int[size];
           for(int i=0;i<size;i++)
           cin>>*(p+i);  // scanf("%d", p)
           cin>>sc;
       }
       void display()
       { for(int i=0;i<size;i++)
           cout<<(*(p+i)*sc)<<" ";
       }
};
int main()
{
    myvector M; // dy
    M.display();
    return 0;
}
